OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FAngela Rayner told MPs today that next
OL,7,Fweek's vote on the Universal Credit
OL,8,Fand Personal Independence Payment bill
OL,9,Fwill go ahead as planned.
OL,11,FShe has been in frontline politics
OL,12,Flong enough to know that this was a
OL,13,Fpassable imitation of a turkey voting
OL,14,Ffor Christmas.
OL,16,FBecause despite her party's humungous
OL,17,Fmajority in the Commons, she and her
OL,18,Fleader Keir Starmer don't have the
OL,19,Fvotes.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
