OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FSo when Labour's party managers
OL,7,Fthreaten uncooperative MPs with being
OL,8,Fexpelled if they vote the wrong way,
OL,9,Fsome say bring it on, that returning
OL,10,Fto civvy street would be a blessed
OL,11,Frelease.
OL,13,FThen there is the almost primal fact
OL,14,Fabout Labour politicians: their
OL,15,Finstincts are that benefits are to be
OL,16,Fincreased, not cut, and most
OL,17,Fespecially not for the vulnerable.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
