OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FSo legislating to take #5 billion from
OL,7,Fdisabled people before being able to
OL,8,Fdemonstrate how these vulnerable
OL,9,Fpeople would be helped into fulfilling
OL,10,Femployment was always going to be
OL,11,Finflammatory.
OL,13,FMonths ago, I put to the Work and
OL,14,FPensions Secretary Liz Kendall on my
OL,15,Fshow that she was making a mistake by
OL,16,Fputting the welfare-cuts cart before
OL,17,Fthe job-creation horse. In reply, she
OL,18,Fobfuscated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
