OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FThe truth is that it was a rushed job,
OL,7,Fdriven by a Chancellor Rachel Reeves
OL,8,Fwho believed she needed the savings to
OL,9,Fpersuade the Office for Budget
OL,10,FResponsibility that she wouldn't
OL,11,Fbreach her own fiscal rules.
OL,13,FIt is the same misjudgement Reeves
OL,14,Fmade when abolishing universal
OL,15,Fentitlement to the winter fuel
OL,16,Fpayment: she decided that manifesting
OL,17,Fher financial prudence to big
OL,18,Finvestors, the buyers of government
OL,19,Fdebt, gilts, was the imperative.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
