OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FBut while it is true that the
OL,7,Fgovernment's borrowing costs are
OL,8,Fpainfully high, and it would be
OL,9,Fdifficult for her if they were to rise
OL,10,Ffurther, it is not obvious that
OL,11,Finvestors would have dumped the pound
OL,12,Fand sterling assets if she had taken
OL,13,Fmore time over the welfare reforms.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
