OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FWhat she could have done was to
OL,7,Fannounce an intention to reform
OL,8,Fdisability benefits in this autumn's
OL,9,Fbudget, when presumably she would have
OL,10,Fbeen better placed to show the
OL,11,Fmechanisms for helping disabled people
OL,12,Ffind and keep paid employment, and
OL,13,Fwhen she would also (probably) be able
OL,14,Fto sweeten the pill by abolishing the
OL,15,Ftwo-child limit on universal credit
OL,16,Fpayments.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
