OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FSo presumably what we'll see in coming
OL,7,Fdays is the government amending its
OL,8,Flegislation to soften the cuts, at the
OL,9,Fpolitical price of being accused of
OL,10,Fyet another u-turn and at considerable
OL,11,Freputational cost to Starmer, Reeves
OL,12,Fand Kendall.
OL,14,FAnd lenders to the government would
OL,15,Falso be jittery, if not despairing.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
