OL,3,CPeston: On welfare reform, Starmer and
OL,4,CReeves lose, whatever the outcome
OL,6,FThere is no painless escape from this
OL,7,Ffor Starmer and Reeves. And there is
OL,8,Fno ambiguity that this is a mess they
OL,9,Fmade for themselves. For the past 11
OL,10,Fmonths may have been blaming the last
OL,11,FConservative governmnent for all their
OL,12,Fprevious woes, but this debacle is
OL,13,Ftheirs alone.
